20/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The relationship between Greece and the United States is maturing, Greek Foreign Ministry spokesman George Koumoutsakos said Thursday (19 May), commenting on the upcoming meeting between Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis with US President George Bush. In an interview with NET TV, Greek Foreign Affairs Minister Petros Molyviatis, who will accompany Karamanlis, expressed his confidence that the bilateral relationship will be further boosted as a result of the visit. (MPA - 20/05/05; ERA, ANA - 19/05/05) 
